<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Key Takeaways</h2>



<ul>
<li>Binance Coin (BNB) network security protocols include encryption and authentication protocols, distributed ledger technology (Blockchain), Proof of Stake (PoS) consensus mechanism, and multi-tier system architecture.</li>



<li>Techniques such as Public Key Infrastructure (PKI), hash functions, Secure Hash Algorithm (SHA), Secure Multi-Party Computation (SMPC), and advanced cryptographic techniques are used to ensure data integrity.</li>



<li>User safety and authentication mechanisms are implemented to secure sensitive user information, reduce the risk of fraudulent activities, and verify user identity.</li>



