<ul>
<li><strong>Monitor your transactions: </strong>Regularly review your wallet activity to spot any unauthorized or unfamiliar transactions. Keep an eye out for any sudden or unexpected movements of your Binance Coin (BNB) or other digital assets.</li>



<li><strong>Stay vigilant for phishing attempts: </strong>Be cautious of any emails or messages asking for your wallet credentials or personal information. Phishing attempts often try to imitate legitimate sources, so always double-check the sender&#8217;s email address or website URL before sharing any sensitive information.</li>



<li><strong>Report suspicious activity immediately:</strong> If you notice any unusual or suspicious activity in your BNB wallet, report it to the appropriate authorities or contact Binance support immediately. Acting promptly can help mitigate any potential losses and protect your digital assets.</li>
</ul>



