<h2 class="wp-block-heading">KYC and AML Policies in Binance Ecosystem</h2>



<p>To ensure compliance with regulations and prevent illicit activities, Binance implements strict KYC (Know Your Customer) and AML (Anti-Money Laundering) policies within its ecosystem. These policies play a vital role in safeguarding investments and maintaining the security of the Binance platform.</p>



<p>KYC procedures require users to verify their identities by submitting relevant documents, such as government-issued identification and proof of address. Binance&#8217;s AML policies involve continuously monitoring transactions for any suspicious activities, such as large and frequent transfers or connections with known criminal entities.</p>



